sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant Dev as Developer
    participant GH as GitHub
    participant CI as CI/CD Pipeline<br/>(Tekton/Konflux)
    participant Quay as Container Registry<br/>quay.io/modh<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Operator as rhods-operator
    participant K8sAPI as OpenShift API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant NCtrl as odh-notebook-controller
    participant Dashboard as RHOAI Dashboard
    participant Browser as User Browser
    participant KRBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Notebook as JupyterLab Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over Dev,Quay: Flow 1: Image Build and Publish
        Dev->>GH: Merge PR (HTTPS/443, TLS 1.3)
        GH->>CI: Trigger build pipeline
        CI->>Quay: Push image (HTTPS/443, TLS 1.3)<br/>Auth: Registry credentials
    end

    rect rgb(255, 248, 240)
        Note over Operator,Dashboard: Flow 2: Platform Deployment
        Operator->>Quay: Pull image by SHA256 digest<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Image pull secret
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update ImageStream<br/>HTTPS/6443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
        Dashboard->>K8sAPI: List ImageStreams<br/>HTTPS/6443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: User Bearer Token
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over Browser,Notebook: Flow 3: User Workbench Access
        Browser->>Dashboard: Select workbench image
        Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Create Notebook CR
        K8sAPI->>NCtrl: Reconcile Notebook CR
        NCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create StatefulSet + Service<br/>(injects kube-rbac-proxy sidecar)
        Browser->>KRBAC: HTTPS/8443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (OIDC)
        KRBAC->>Notebook: HTTP/8888 (pod-local)<br/>No TLS, No auth
        Notebook-->>KRBAC: Response
        KRBAC-->>Browser: HTTPS Response
    end

    rect rgb(255, 240, 255)
        Note over CI,K8sAPI: Flow 4: Elyra Pipeline Execution
        participant PCtrl as Elyra Pipeline Controller
        participant Runtime as Runtime Container<br/>(headless)
        participant S3 as Object Storage (S3)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

        PCtrl->>Quay: Pull runtime image<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Image pull secret
        PCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create pipeline pod<br/>HTTPS/6443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
        Runtime->>S3: Read/Write artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: AWS credentials
        Runtime-->>PCtrl: Pipeline step complete
    end
